         <abstract id="aspace_f0c0ae237b702d06d1830ce0d0722c3a">The Raymond Deghels papers document the life and career of a Belgian inventor who created a non-reflective paint to disguise military aircraft during World War II. The collection contains literary manuscripts, patents and supporting material such as paint samples, correspondence, legal documents, photographs, and personal effects.</abstract>
